Summary

contract hardening day

Today was about making Command Center behave like a stable shell instead of a visually fragile prototype. The work was less about adding surface area and more about removing contradictions between what the layout claimed and what it actually did under scroll, rail placement, and panel hierarchy changes.

The main theme was truth alignment in the UI shell: the rail now moves to the correct side instead of only flipping internal flex direction, lens panes scroll inside their own containment instead of pushing the page around, and the shell hierarchy has clearer surface boundaries and state presentation. In parallel, the context directive and PI contract coverage were restored so the shell invariants are guarded by tests rather than left as implied behavior.

