Important outcome

Command Center is no longer just visually rearranged. It now has enough structural truth to behave as a shell with real containment, real rail placement, and real contract boundaries.

The system stopped pretending layout changes were enough on their own, and started enforcing the things that make the shell stable under use: scroll locality, side switching, and test-backed invariants.

